There are lots of thread here on charm soloing but the basics are pretty easy....<br>
<br>
1 - Select pet, try to get one with a lower MR (this is based on experience)<br>
<br>
2 - Tash pet<br>
<br>
3 - Charm pet (some people will mezz to make charm easier to get on).<br>
<br>
4 - If duoed with a ranger/druid snare before charm<br>
<br>
5 - Find mob to kill<br>
<br>
6 - Tash mob<br>
<br>
7 - Root mob<br>
<br>
8 - Send in pet<br>
<br>
9 - Cause at least 1 point of damage<br>
<br>
10 - Rinse/Repeat<br>
<br>
On pet breaks, be prepared for it...Rune and an HP buff are great as is Spell haste (for recharming).  Some people like their pets hasted which is a faster way to kill but a bit more dangerous.  Slowing the target mob can make your pet last longer, alternatively you can kill your pet after he kills the target mob and get full xp for him.<br>
<br>
As per the aa/15 mins, that was some time ago.  On top of the xp changes, they have changed both Command of Druzzil to have a much smaller MR adjust.  This has reduced the effectivity of this spell dramatically.<br>
<br>
I generally solo not in PoV but in PoN or PoD while waiting for groups.  Its safer and is better than sitting around.<br>
<br>
Now if you want to talk about aa/min kings....its bards.  They made this a lot more dangerous by having some mobs in HOH summon but they used to be able to swarm kite HOH and get 6 - 8 AAs per pull.<br>
